"Motagh M., Walter T.R., Sharifi M.A., Fielding E., Schenk A., Anderssohn J., Zschau J.","Land subsidence in Iran caused by widespread water reservoir overexploitation",2008,"Geophysical Research Letters","35","16", L16403,"","",,,10.1029/2008GL033814,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-56449091355&partnerID=40&md5=eb4acbc70f3d69e9eb0d48fba1a25188","Department of Earthquake Risk and Early Warning, GeoForschungsZentrum, Telegrafenberg Haus E, Potsdam D-14473, Germany; Department of Geomatics and Surveying Engineering, University of Tehran, Tehran, Iran; Jet Propulsion Laboratory, California Institute of Technology, Pasadena, CA 91109, United States; Geodetic Institute, Universität Karlsruhe, D-76131 Karlsruhe, Germany; Department of Remote Sensing, GeoForschungsZentrum (GFZ), D-14473 Potsdam, Germany","Motagh, M., Department of Earthquake Risk and Early Warning, GeoForschungsZentrum, Telegrafenberg Haus E, Potsdam D-14473, Germany, Department of Geomatics and Surveying Engineering, University of Tehran, Tehran, Iran; Walter, T.R., Department of Earthquake Risk and Early Warning, GeoForschungsZentrum, Telegrafenberg Haus E, Potsdam D-14473, Germany; Sharifi, M.A., Department of Geomatics and Surveying Engineering, University of Tehran, Tehran, Iran; Fielding, E., Jet Propulsion Laboratory, California Institute of Technology, Pasadena, CA 91109, United States; Schenk, A., Geodetic Institute, Universität Karlsruhe, D-76131 Karlsruhe, Germany; Anderssohn, J., Department of Remote Sensing, GeoForschungsZentrum (GFZ), D-14473 Potsdam, Germany; Zschau, J., Department of Earthquake Risk and Early Warning, GeoForschungsZentrum, Telegrafenberg Haus E, Potsdam D-14473, Germany","The increasing demands upon groundwater resources due to expanding metropolitan and agricultural areas are a serious challenge, particularly in semiarid and and regions. In Iran, decades of unrestrained groundwater extraction for domestic, agricultural, and industrial use have resulted in a precipitous depletion of this valuable resource. Here we show that the decline in groundwater. levels is associated with land-surface deformation on local and regional scales. Combining water-level data with satellite radar observations provides evidence for the prevalence of compacting aquifers in the country. Groundwater level decline is often associated with destruction of the aquifers, which appears to be a common problem in the groundwater basins. of central and northeast Iran. Global wanning and future climate change will affect and and semiarid areas in the coming decades, further augmenting hazards associated with groundwater-induced land subsidence. Copyright 2008 by the American Geophysical Union.",,"Aquifers; Climate change; Climatology; Groundwater; Hydrogeology; Industrial applications; Reservoirs (water); Subsidence; Underground reservoirs; Agricultural areas; Common problems; Future climates; Groundwater basins; Groundwater extractions; Groundwater levels; Industrial uses; Land subsidences; Regional scales; Satellite radars; Semi-arid; Semiarid areas; Surface deformations; Water reservoirs; Groundwater resources; aquifer; climate change; exploitation; global warming; groundwater; reservoir; subsidence; water level; Asia; Eurasia; Iran; Middle East",,,,,,"Amelung, F., Galloway, D.L., Bell, J.W., Zebker, H.A., Laczniak, R.J., Sensing the ups and downs of Las Vegas: InSAR reveals structural control of land subsidence and aquifer-system deformation (1999) Geology, 27 (6), pp. 483-486; Anderssohn, J., Wetzel, H.L., Walter, T.R., Motagh, M., Djamour, Y., Kaufmann, H., Land subsidence pattern controlled by old alpine basement faults in the Kashmar Valley, northeast Iran: Results from InSAR and levelling (2008) Geophys. J. Int, 174, pp. 287-294. , doi:10.1111/ j.1365-246X.2008.03805.x; Bell, J.W., Amelung, F., Ramelli, A.R., Blewitt, G., Land subsidence in Las Vegas, Nevada, 1935-2000: New geodetic data show evolution, revised spatial patterns, and reduce